The paper discusses a new approach to planning for autonomous agents, specifically robots, that covers both kinematic and dynamic aspects of motion. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel type of damping forces, which could fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The use of the HPF approach to planning also suggests that the paper could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper may also involve machine learning techniques, which could place it in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper may involve computer vision techniques, as it discusses the guidance of autonomous agents, which could place it in the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category.
